# QP Megathread CODEOWNERS
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# This file restricts who can approve changes to certain paths.
# For CODEOWNERS to actually BLOCK merges you also need a Ruleset
# (or branch protection rule) on `main` with
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled.
#
# Pattern precedence: the LAST matching pattern wins, so more
# specific overrides come after broader rules.
#
# Locked to maintainers:
#   - index.html
#   - /assets/css, /assets/js, /assets/data
#   - CNAME, .github
#
# Open to the community (no review required):
#   - /pages/**          (all subpages)
#   - /assets/images/**  (logos, icons, screenshots, etc.)
# ------------------------------------------------------------

# Lock the index and shared code/data assets to maintainers
/index.html           @KaladinDMP
/assets/              @KaladinDMP
/CNAME                @KaladinDMP
/.github/             @KaladinDMP

# --- Community-open exceptions (must come AFTER the broad rules) ---

# Anyone can add images, logos or screenshots without review.
# Empty owner list = no review required.
/assets/images/

# Subpages are intentionally open: /pages/** is not listed,
# so no Code Owner review is required there either.
